name: Semi Squat Jump (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Jump explosively, extending your hips and knees while swinging your arms for momentum. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next repetition. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Drop Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump up explosively, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:4 While in mid-air, quickly bring your feet together. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately drop back into a squat position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump explosively off the ground, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:4 While in mid-air, quickly bring your arms forward for balance. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next repetition. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jump Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump explosively, extending your hips and knees fully. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately lower your body back into a squat position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Burpee
secondary_muscles: quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, shoulders, triceps, core
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, placing the dumbbells on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Kick your feet back into a push-up position, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Perform a push-up, bending your elbows and lowering your chest towards the ground. | Step:5 Jump your feet back towards your hands, landing in a squat position. | Step:6 Stand up explosively, lifting the dumbbells off the ground and bringing them to your shoulders. | Step:7 Press the dumbbells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Lower the dumbbells back to your shoulders and repeat the entire sequence for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Box Jump Down With One Leg Stabilization
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a box or platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and jump onto the box, landing softly with one foot on the box and the other foot hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Stabilize yourself on the box with the foot that is on it, while keeping the other foot off the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, engaging your calf muscles to maintain balance. | Step:5 Slowly step down with the foot that is on the box, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the exercise with the other leg.

name: Astride Jumps (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Jump explosively upwards, extending your legs and arms. | Step:4 While in the air, spread your legs apart and bring your arms out to the sides. | Step:5 Land softly with your feet shoulder-width apart, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Star Jump (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and jump up explosively. | Step:3 As you jump, spread your legs and extend your arms out to the sides, forming a star shape with your body. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet with your knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scissor Jumps (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Jump off the ground and simultaneously cross your right leg in front of your left leg. | Step:3 As you land, quickly switch legs, crossing your left leg in front of your right leg. | Step:4 Continue alternating legs and jumping as quickly as possible. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Forward Jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Swing your arms back for momentum. | Step:4 Jump forward explosively, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next jump. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jack Jump (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Jump up, spreading your feet apart and raising your arms above your head. | Step:3 As you land, quickly jump back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump With Complex
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. Maintain complex form throughout. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Backward Jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and jump backwards, pushing off with both feet. | Step:3 Land softly on the balls of your feet, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunge With Jump
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Push off with your right foot and jump into the air, switching the position of your feet mid-air. | Step:4 Land softly with your left foot forward and immediately lower your body into a lunge position. | Step:5 Continue alternating between lunges and jumps for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Single Leg Squat (Pistol) Male
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Lift your right foot off the ground and extend it forward. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body down by bending your left knee and pushing your hips back. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight as you lower yourself down. | Step:5 Lower until your left thigh is parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Side Wrist Pull Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Extend your right arm out to the side, parallel to the ground, with your palm facing down. | Step:3 With your left hand, grab your right hand and gently pull it towards your body, feeling a stretch in your right forearm. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Squat To Overhead Reach With Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you come up from the squat, raise your arms overhead and twist your torso to one side. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the squat, this time twisting your torso to the opposite side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides with each squat repetition.

name: Hyperextension (On Bench)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the hyperextension bench so that your hips are resting comfortably on the pad and your feet are secured. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. | Step:3 Slowly lower your upper body towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise your upper body back up until it is in line with your legs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverse Leg Curl (Bench Support)
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a bench with your hips at the edge and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Hold onto the bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper body still, bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a leg curl machine with your legs extended and your ankles hooked under the padded lever. | Step:2 Place your hands on the side handles of the machine for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your hamstrings. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position while inhaling. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull Up (Neutral Grip)
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbows and driving your elbows down towards your hips. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: L-Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your lats and biceps to pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Grip Rear Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with a wide overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sissy Squat Isolation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body by bending your knees and leaning back, keeping your torso upright. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as far as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Emphasize isolation control.

name: Inverse Leg Curl (On Pull-Up Cable Machine)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the ankle straps are at the lowest setting. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your legs extended and the ankle straps attached to your feet. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles of the bench for stability. | Step:4 Bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squat To Overhead Reach
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Lower your body down into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you come up from the squat, extend your arms overhead, reaching towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Return to the starting position by lowering your arms and bending your knees to squat down again. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Potty Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Lower your body down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back as if you were sitting on a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip (On Dip-Pull-Up Cage)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the dip bars to a height that allows you to comfortably grip them. | Step:2 Stand between the bars and place your hands on each bar, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Jump up and straighten your arms, supporting your body weight on the bars. | Step:4 Bend your knees and cross your ankles behind you. | Step:5 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your chest up and your shoulders down. | Step:6 Continue lowering until your shoulders are below your elbows or until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:7 Push through your palms and extend your elbows to raise your body back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rocky Pull-Up Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a pull-up bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a mat or bench with your legs extended. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides or under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lift your feet off the ground, bringing your thighs towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stalder Press
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended overhead. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position while keeping your arms extended overhead. | Step:4 As you squat down, press your arms down towards the ground, engaging your triceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to stand back up while simultaneously raising your arms back overhead. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Slow Leg Pull In Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain slow form throughout.

name: Push And Pull Bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 From the push-up position, pull your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:5 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a suspension trainer with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and place the top of your foot in the foot cradle of the suspension trainer. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your chest up and your knee in line with your toes. | Step:4 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Reverse Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Arm Against Wall Compressed
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out in front of you and place your palm against the wall. | Step:3 Engage your core and lean your body forward, keeping your arm straight and your back flat. Maintain compressed form throughout. | Step:4 Slowly push against the wall with your palm, activating your lat muscles. | Step:5 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and repeat with the other arm.

name: Archer Pull Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 As you pull yourself up, bend one arm and bring your elbow towards your side, while keeping the other arm straight. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar and your bent arm is fully flexed. | Step:5 Lower yourself back down with control, straightening the bent arm and repeating the movement on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides with each repetition.

name: Bodyweight Kneeling Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Kneel down on the ground with your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you, shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Extend your legs straight behind you, balancing on your toes and hands, forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your upper body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Potty Squat With Support
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable support, such as a chair or wall, for balance. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sissy Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body by bending your knees and leaning back, keeping your torso upright. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as far as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapular Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Retract your shoulder blades by pulling them down and back. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, focusing on squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Split Squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and place it about two feet in front of the other foot. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, and your back knee is hovering just above the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Inverted Style Inverse Leg Curl (On Pull-Up Cable Machine)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the ankle straps are at the lowest setting. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your legs extended and the ankle straps attached to your feet. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles of the bench for stability. | Step:4 Bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain inverted form throughout.

name: Lower Back Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your stomach with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, and slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling your back upwards. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hyperextension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the hyperextension bench so that your upper thighs are resting on the pad and your feet are secured. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. | Step:3 Lower your upper body towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise your upper body back up until it is in line with your legs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull yourself up by bending your elbows, bringing your chest towards the bar. | Step:3 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl (On Floor)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:3 Lift your hips off the ground, engaging your glutes and hamstrings. | Step:4 Slowly curl your legs towards your glutes, keeping your hips lifted. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Lower your hips back down to the ground. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Curtsey Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step diagonally behind and across your body with your right foot, crossing it behind your left leg. | Step:3 Bend both knees as if you were curtsying, lowering your body towards the ground. | Step:4 Keep your torso upright and your weight on your front foot. | Step:5 Push through your front foot to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping diagonally behind and across your body with your left foot.

name: Rear Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other leg.

name: Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbows and bringing your chest towards the bar. | Step:4 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg Pull In Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Leg Squat - Expanded Variation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other leg. Maintain expanded form throughout.

name: Bench Pull-Ups
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under a bar or a sturdy horizontal surface that is at chest height. | Step:2 Grab the bar or surface with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Pull your chest towards the bar or surface by squeezing your shoulder blades together and bending your elbows. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar or surface. | Step:6 Lower yourself back down to the starting position with control. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shoulder Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with a shoulder-width grip, palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Hang freely with your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Sumo Pull Through
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointed outwards. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands in front of your body, arms extended. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips down into a squat position, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell down between your legs, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Drive through your heels and extend your hips forward, pulling the dumbbell up and in front of your body. | Step:6 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, then lower the dumbbell back down between your legs. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Swing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold the kettlebell with both hands in front of your body, arms extended. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips, pushing your butt back. | Step:4 Swing the kettlebell back between your legs, keeping your arms straight and maintaining a flat back. | Step:5 Drive your hips forward and swing the kettlebell up to shoulder height, using the momentum generated by your hips. | Step:6 Allow the kettlebell to swing back down between your legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Floor Fly (With Barbell)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell until your arms are parallel to the floor, feeling a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell resting on your right thigh. | Step:2 Extend your left leg straight out in front of you, keeping your foot flexed. | Step:3 Place the ball of your right foot on an elevated surface, such as a step or weight plate. | Step:4 Using your calf muscles, raise your right heel as high as possible. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Dumbbell Standing Bent Over Two Arm Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Squat Calf Raise On Leg Press Machine
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leg press machine so that your knees are slightly bent when your feet are on the footplate. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the footplate, shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Place your toes and the balls of your feet on the footplate, keeping your heels off the edge. | Step:4 Release the safety handles and push the footplate away from you by extending your knees. | Step:5 Once your knees are fully extended, slowly lower your heels by flexing your calves. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the footplate back up by extending your calves. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up Close-Grip Off Dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands placed close together, directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, resting them on the ground. | Step:3 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, landing on the ball of your foot. | Step:3 Bend both knees to lower your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Forward Lunge Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight overhead, keeping your elbows close to your ears. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then straighten your arms to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Barbell Full Zercher Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in the crooks of your elbows, with your hands gripping the barbell for stability. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you lower your hips back and down into a squat position. | Step:4 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:5 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat (Side Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Standing Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and bring it down to shoulder level, with your palms facing forward. | Step:4 Press the barbell upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Full Range Of Motion
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the lat pulldown machine with your knees positioned under the pads. | Step:2 Grasp the cable bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lean back slightly and keep your chest up, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Vertical Pallof Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and wrap the band around a sturdy object at chest height. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands and step away from the anchor point, creating tension in the band. | Step:3 Position yourself perpendicular to the anchor point, with your side facing the band. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, keeping your hands at chest height. | Step:5 Engage your core and press the band away from your chest, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Hold the position for a few seconds, then slowly bring the band back towards your chest. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Smith Standing Back Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upwards, bringing the barbell towards your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band under your feet. | Step:2 Hold the band with your palms facing forward and raise your hands to shoulder height, elbows bent. | Step:3 Press the band overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the band back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Seated Two Arm Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead by extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebells back to shoulder level. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Close Grip To Skull Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and hold a barbell with a close grip. | Step:2 Lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms to press the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Front Raise Over Head
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Slowly raise the barbell in front of you, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until the barbell is slightly above shoulder level. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spell Caster
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the waist, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arm with the dumbbell towards the opposite foot, rotating your torso as you do so. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever One Arm Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the lever handle with one hand and position your elbow at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Press the lever upward until your arm is fully extended overhead. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the lever back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell Hack Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell behind your legs, resting it on your upper thighs. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending at the knees and hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Pistol Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Lift your left foot off the ground and extend it forward, keeping it parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your right foot flat on the ground and your left leg extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Smith Wide Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a comfortable position on the smith machine. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows out to the sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Arm Side Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and lower the barbell towards the outside of your leg, keeping your arm straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Lower the barbell as far as you can while maintaining good form. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your forearm on your thigh. | Step:3 Allow your wrist to extend, letting the dumbbell roll down towards your fingers. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrist back up, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells to your sides with a slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the cables at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing away from the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Step forward slightly to create tension in the cables. | Step:5 Keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:6 With a slight bend in your elbows, slowly bring your arms forward and together in front of your chest. | Step:7 Squeeze your chest muscles at the peak of the movement. | Step:8 Slowly reverse the movement, returning your arms to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upper Chest Crossovers
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the cables at chest height. | Step:2 Stand in the center of the cable machine with one foot slightly in front of the other. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with your palms facing down and your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the cables together in front of your chest, crossing them over each other. | Step:6 Squeeze your chest muscles at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the cables back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Incline Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back resting against an incline bench. | Step:2 Hold a cable handle in one hand and position your arm at a 90-degree angle with your elbow bent. | Step:3 Press the cable handle forward and upward, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Smith Machine Decline Close Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench on the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Seated Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lean back and position the dumbbells to the sides of your chest, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Pull Through
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at ground level. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step forward to create tension in the band, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Hinge at the hips and push your glutes back, maintaining a slight bend in your knees. | Step:5 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:6 Drive your hips forward and squeeze your glutes to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, lower your body down by bending at the knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in one hand and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the dumbbell at shoulder level with your palm facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Band Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands, palms facing up, and rest your forearms on your thighs. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Scott Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Low Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at a height that allows you to comfortably rest it on your upper back. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outwards. | Step:3 Step under the bar and position it across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:4 Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Unrack the bar by straightening your legs and stepping back from the rack. | Step:6 Take a deep breath and brace your core. | Step:7 Initiate the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:8 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:9 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:10 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:11 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Shoulder Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lift the barbell up to shoulder height, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Slowly raise the barbell overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to shoulder height. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it towards your upper chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Wide Grip Rear Pulldown Behind Neck
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulldown bar is at a height above your head. | Step:2 Sit down on the seat and grab the pulldown bar with a wide overhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your chest up as you lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Palm-In Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Plant your feet firmly on the ground and keep your back straight against the bench. | Step:4 Start with the dumbbells at shoulder level, elbows bent and palms facing each other. | Step:5 Press the dumbbells up and away from your body, extending your arms fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Shoulder Press (Parallel Grip)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inward. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Jm Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in close to your body. | Step:4 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and lift the barbell forward and upward until it reaches shoulder level. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Revers Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on the bench, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the dumbbells towards your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Lunge Pass Through
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, pass the kettlebell under your right thigh and transfer it to your left hand. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot to return to the starting position, while simultaneously passing the kettlebell back to your right hand. | Step:5 Repeat the lunge on the opposite side, passing the kettlebell under your left thigh. | Step:6 Continue alternating lunges and passing the kettlebell between hands for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Pullover On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball and roll forward until your upper back is resting on the ball. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head while keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Jm Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in close to your body. | Step:4 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Incline Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back against an incline bench. | Step:2 Hold a cable handle in one hand with your arm extended and palm facing inward. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbow, slowly lower your arm out to the side until your hand is in line with your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring your arm back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Around Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet firmly on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head in an arc motion. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Forward Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your arms fully extended in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise the cable handle up to shoulder level. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Palms In Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, press the dumbbells upwards until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Bent-Over Hip Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at ankle height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back to create tension in the band, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Hinge at the hips and lean forward, maintaining a neutral spine. | Step:5 Extend your right leg straight back, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Lower your right leg back down and repeat with the left leg. | Step:7 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold onto the cable machine handles or attach a cable ankle strap to your ankles. | Step:3 Raise your heels off the ground by extending your ankles as high as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and position it at shoulder height, with your elbow bent and palm facing forward. | Step:3 Slowly press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended, while keeping your core engaged and maintaining balance on the exercise ball. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Arm Rotate
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and hold a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell up to shoulder height, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:3 Rotate your forearm outward, away from your body, while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly rotate your forearm back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Slowly lift the dumbbells in front of you, with your arms straight, until they are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Hyperextension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the leverage machine to fit your body and secure your feet in the foot pads. | Step:2 Lie face down on the machine with your upper body hanging off the edge and your hips resting on the pad. | Step:3 Cross your arms over your chest or place them behind your head. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your legs upward until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Bent Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and press the kettlebell overhead with your right arm, keeping your elbow locked. | Step:3 Rotate your torso to the left, shifting your weight onto your left foot. | Step:4 Bend your left knee and lower your torso towards the ground, keeping your right arm extended overhead. | Step:5 As you lower, keep your eyes on the kettlebell and your chest lifted. | Step:6 Once your left hand touches the ground, push through your left foot and straighten your left leg, driving your hips forward. | Step:7 As you drive your hips forward, use your core and right arm to press the kettlebell back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in front of your shoulders, resting it on your collarbone and shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:5 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on the bench with your wrist hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrist upwards, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell Jefferson Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, resting it on the front of your body, just below your waist. | Step:3 Step your left foot forward and your right foot back, keeping your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:5 Push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, alternating your forward and back foot with each repetition.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing towards your body. | Step:2 Place your feet flat on the ground and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upwards until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Band Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the band handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, pushing the bands away from your chest. | Step:4 Slowly lower the bands back down to your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Arnold Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support and hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level, palms facing your body and elbows bent. | Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended and your palms are facing forward. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists as you lift, so that your palms end up facing forward at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise one dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm straight and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:7 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean forward slightly and keep your back straight. | Step:5 Pull the bar down towards your thighs by extending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing inwards and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Place your other hand on your hip for stability. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upwards, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Standing Around World
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides at shoulder height, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, slowly rotate your arms in a circular motion, bringing the dumbbells in front of your body and then overhead. | Step:4 Continue the circular motion, bringing the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Hack Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable position for your height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart on the platform, toes slightly pointed outwards. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles or bars for stability. | Step:4 Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:5 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to raise your body back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight and chest up, and grip the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift the bar by extending your hips and knees, keeping the bar close to your body. | Step:5 Stand up straight, fully extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Lower the bar back down by bending at the hips and knees, maintaining control and keeping your back straight. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Twisting Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band under your feet. | Step:2 Hold the band handles at shoulder height with your palms facing forward. | Step:3 Engage your core and press the band overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 As you press, twist your torso to one side, keeping your hips stable. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the press and twist on the opposite side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lateral Raise (Support Head)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Wide-Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang at arm's length in front of your thighs, with your palms facing away from your body. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell upward by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing your knees to bend slightly. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, then push through your heels and engage your glutes to return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rear Lunge V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, landing on the ball of your foot. | Step:3 Bend both knees to lower your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other leg.

name: Kettlebell Double Push Press
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Initiate the movement by explosively extending your hips, knees, and ankles, driving the kettlebells overhead. | Step:4 As the kettlebells reach the top, press them fully overhead, locking out your arms. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebells back to the starting position by bending your elbows and bringing them back down to shoulder height. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Deep Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Double Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Bend your knees and quickly drop into a partial squat. | Step:5 Explosively extend your hips and knees, driving the kettlebells overhead. | Step:6 Lock out your arms and catch the kettlebells overhead with your knees slightly bent. | Step:7 Stand up straight and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lateral Pulldown (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to the cable machine at a high position. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the tension and allow the rope to return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Guillotine Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell slowly towards your neck, keeping your elbows pointed outwards. | Step:4 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your neck. | Step:5 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twin Handle Parallel Grip Lat Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and position your thighs under the thigh pads, keeping your feet flat on the floor. | Step:4 Lean back slightly and keep your chest up, maintaining a neutral spine. | Step:5 Pull the handles down towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lats. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Seated Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench in front of a Smith machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the barbell towards your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Hip Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable to a low pulley and stand facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Place the cable around your ankle and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:4 Slowly extend your leg straight back, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:7 Switch sides and repeat with the other leg.

name: Trap Bar Deadlift
