instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the trap bar on the ground in front of you. | Step:2 Bend at the hips and knees to lower yourself down and grip the handles of the trap bar with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and chest up as you begin to lift the trap bar off the ground by extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As you lift, focus on driving through your heels and squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Lower the trap bar back down to the ground by bending at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl Lunge With Bowling Motion
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, bending your right knee and lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 At the bottom of the lunge, rotate your torso to the right, as if you were bowling a ball. | Step:5 Reverse the motion, stepping back with your right foot and returning to the starting position while lowering the dumbbells back down. | Step:6 Repeat the lunge and curl motion, this time rotating your torso to the left. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Low Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the low pulleys of a cable machine and select an appropriate weight. | Step:2 Stand in the middle of the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Maintaining control, slowly bring your arms forward in a sweeping motion, crossing them in front of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, feeling the stretch in your chest muscles. | Step:6 Reverse the motion and slowly return your arms to the starting position, keeping tension on your chest muscles throughout. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your hamstrings and glutes to lift the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Zercher Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in the crooks of your elbows, with your hands gripping the bar for stability. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you lower your hips back and down into a squat position. | Step:4 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cuban Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, press the dumbbells straight up overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back down to shoulder height, rotating your wrists back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Underhand Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a high anchor point, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy beam. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Engage your lats and pull the band down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell W-Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 45-degree incline. | Step:2 Attach the cable handles to the high pulleys. | Step:3 Sit on the bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:4 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and bring them to shoulder height. | Step:5 Push the handles forward and upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the handles are at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and bring them up to shoulder level, with your elbows bent and pointing outwards. | Step:4 Press the handles upwards until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternate Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable machine with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lean back slightly and pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly twist your torso to one side, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly rotate back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the twist to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Landmine 180
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell with both hands in front of your chest. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and rotate your torso to the right, swinging the barbell down towards your right hip. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the movement, quickly reverse the motion and rotate your torso to the left, swinging the barbell up and across your body towards your left shoulder. | Step:4 Continue this twisting motion, alternating sides, for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand and extend your arms straight up above your chest, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells slowly to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell on the ground in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and hinge at the hips to lower your torso and grip the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and chest lifted as you drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As you stand up straight, squeeze your glutes and keep your core engaged. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the ground by bending at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Fixed Back Underhand Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point above your head. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Step back to create tension in the band, keeping your arms fully extended. | Step:5 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pull the band down towards your chest, leading with your elbows. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lats. | Step:8 Slowly release the tension in the band and return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Shoulder Press V. 3
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest of the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles of the machine with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push the handles upward and forward until your arms are fully extended, but not locked. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Plyo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the squat, explode upward, jumping off the ground. | Step:4 While in the air, quickly switch the position of your feet, landing with your opposite foot forward. | Step:5 Immediately lower your body back into a squat position and repeat the jump, switching your feet again. | Step:6 Continue alternating the position of your feet with each jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Hack Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the barbell on the smith machine to an appropriate height for your body. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly pointed outwards. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper traps and shoulders. | Step:4 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you unrack the barbell. | Step:6 Take a step back and position your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:7 Bend your knees and lower your body down, keeping your chest up and back straight. | Step:8 Continue descending until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:9 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:10 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Squat
instructions: Step:1 Place a dumbbell on the ground in front of a bench. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the bench with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at the knees and hips to lower yourself down towards the bench, keeping your chest up and back straight. | Step:4 Once your glutes touch the bench, push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lean back on the bench and raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Keeping your back against the bench, exhale and raise the dumbbells above your head, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Lying Calf Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable weight. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the platform. | Step:3 Place your toes and the balls of your feet on the edge of the platform, with your heels hanging off. | Step:4 Push the platform away from you by extending your ankles, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Continue pushing until your calves are fully contracted. | Step:6 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower the platform back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Finger Curls
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your fingers towards your palms, squeezing the barbell tightly. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly release your fingers back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Standing Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your hands at chest level. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the handles back towards your chest, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball On The Wall Calf Raise (Tennis Ball Between Ankles)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place an exercise ball between the wall and your lower back. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms extended by your sides. | Step:4 Place a tennis ball between your ankles. | Step:5 Raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the incline bench to a 30-45 degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:3 Lie back on the bench, keeping your feet flat on the ground. | Step:4 Hold the dumbbell with your arm extended straight up over your chest. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell out to the side in a wide arc, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:6 Pause when your arm is parallel to the ground, then reverse the motion to bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Smith Standing Behind Head Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height of the smith machine so that the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lift the bar off the rack and step back, maintaining a stable stance. | Step:5 Position the bar behind your head, resting on your upper traps. | Step:6 Keep your core engaged and your chest lifted throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Press the bar overhead by extending your arms, fully straightening them. | Step:8 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pullover To Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, lower the barbell behind your head in an arc-like motion until you feel a stretch in your lats. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then reverse the motion and press the barbell back to the starting position above your chest. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Arnold Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing towards you. | Step:2 Engage your core and press the kettlebells overhead, rotating your palms to face forward as you extend your arms. | Step:3 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the kettlebells back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying On Floor Rear Delt Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Engaging your shoulder muscles, lift your arms up and out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball On The Wall Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and place an exercise ball between your lower back and the wall. | Step:2 Position your feet shoulder-width apart, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms extended by your sides. | Step:4 Raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Judo Flip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands at chest level, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and rotate your torso to the right, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 As you rotate, pivot your back foot and allow your hips to rotate naturally. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully and finish the movement by flipping the cable handle over your shoulder. | Step:6 Return to the starting position by reversing the movement, rotating your torso back to the center. | Step:7 Repeat the movement on the opposite side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Cross-Over Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to each side of a cable machine at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand in the middle of the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and step back to create tension in the cables. | Step:4 Lean forward slightly from the hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:5 Pull the handles down and across your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your hands at shoulder level. | Step:3 Push the handles upward until your arms are fully extended, but do not lock your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Hip Adduction
instructions: Step:1 Attach the ankle cuff to your ankle and stand facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Position yourself far enough away from the machine so that there is tension on the cable. | Step:3 Place your hands on the machine for support. | Step:4 Keeping your leg straight, slowly move your leg across your body towards the midline. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the smith machine to a comfortable incline angle. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip that is slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the bar and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the bar is just above your chest. | Step:6 Push the bar back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Advanced Dumbbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing a slight bend in your knees. Focus on advanced movement. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, then squeeze your glutes and push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wall Style Dumbbell Pullover Hip Extension On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and the dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the exercise ball down your back until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your arms straight and maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 While keeping your arms extended, lift your hips off the ground, squeezing your glutes and engaging your core. | Step:7 (wall variation) Lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twisting Pull With Intensified
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and step away from the machine, extending your arm fully. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart, with your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your torso to the right as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position, keeping tension on the cable. | Step:8 (intensified variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform with your right hand.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press On Exercise Ball Modified
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand, feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell at shoulder height with your palm facing forward. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. Emphasize modified control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Sled 45 Degrees One Leg Press Pointed
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the footplate. Perform with pointed intensity. | Step:3 Place one foot on the footplate and extend your leg, pushing the sled away from you. | Step:4 Slowly bend your knee and lower the sled back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Military Press With Strength
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Push the handles upward until your arms are fully extended, but do not lock your elbows. | Step:4 (strength variation) Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Underhand Pulldown With Classic
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a high anchor point, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy beam. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Emphasize classic control. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Engage your lats and pull the band down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Gentle Style Dumbbell One Leg Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Place one foot on the ground and extend the other leg straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly and bring your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells down and out to the sides, feeling a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 (gentle variation) Pause for a moment at the bottom, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Contracted Kettlebell Extended Range One Arm Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in one hand, with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow locked and your wrist straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm. Emphasize contracted control.

name: Triple Style Sled One Leg Calf Press On Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leg press machine so that your knees are slightly bent when your feet are on the sled. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the sled, shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Place your toes and the balls of your feet on the sled, keeping your heels off. | Step:4 Push the sled forward by extending your ankles, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the sled back down by flexing your ankles. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Perform with triple intensity.

name: Dumbbell Iron Cross - Improved Variation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, forming a T shape with your body. Perform with improved intensity. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Reverse Grip Bench Press Horizontal
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide reverse grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in and your wrists straight. Focus on horizontal movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intense Barbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. Maintain intense form throughout. | Step:5 Engage your hamstrings and glutes to lift the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Light Lever Standing Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your hands at chest level. Maintain light form throughout. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the handles back towards your chest, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Shoulder Press With Declined
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the resistance band with both hands, palms facing forward, and bring it up to shoulder level. | Step:3 Press the band overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the band back down to shoulder level. Emphasize declined control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bent Arm Pullover - Powerful Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a shoulder-width grip and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the barbell behind your head while keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on powerful movement.

name: Inverted Style Smith Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that the handles are at shoulder level. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and lift them off the supports, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the handles down to shoulder level, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Press the handles up overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to shoulder level. Maintain inverted form throughout. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Macro Style Weighted One Hand Pull Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arm fully extended and your body straight. Perform with macro intensity. | Step:3 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbow and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Side Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one dumbbell overhead while keeping the other dumbbell at shoulder height. | Step:3 Lower the pressed dumbbell back to shoulder height while pressing the other dumbbell overhead. | Step:4 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Pullover On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with one hand and extend your arm straight up above your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head while keeping your arm straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Smith Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and footplate of the smith machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Push the footplate away from you by extending your legs, keeping your back against the backrest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position. | Step:6 Slowly bend your knees and lower the footplate back towards you, returning to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells towards your chest, allowing your elbows to flare out to the sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Pronation
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your chest facing down and your arms extended straight down, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Rotate your palms so they are facing up. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells as you rotate your palms to face down. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Leg Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Place one foot on the ground and extend the other leg straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly and bring your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells down and out to the sides, feeling a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Cable Lying Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the cables and lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the handles with your palms facing each other and your arms extended straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lower your arms out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring your arms back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the dumbbells towards your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Figure 8
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Pass the kettlebell between your legs, switching hands as it reaches the back of your legs. | Step:4 As the kettlebell comes forward, pass it to the other hand between your legs. | Step:5 Continue passing the kettlebell between your legs in a figure 8 motion. | Step:6 Maintain a steady pace and engage your core throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Calf Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the machine so that your shoulders are aligned with the lever pad. | Step:2 Place your toes on the lower portion of the platform and position your knees under the lever pad. | Step:3 Grasp the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Press the lever pad down by extending your ankles, lifting your heels as high as possible. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Anti Gravity Press
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding the ez barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Raise the barbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbows slightly bent and your palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the barbell overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Thruster
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Lower into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the squat, explosively drive through your heels to stand up, simultaneously pressing the kettlebell overhead. | Step:4 Lock out your arms at the top of the movement, fully extending your elbows. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position by reversing the movement, bending your elbows and lowering the weight back to your chest. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rack Pull
instructions: Step:1 Set up a barbell on a rack at knee height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outwards. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and knees to lower yourself down and grip the barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift the barbell by extending your hips and knees, pulling your shoulders back and squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position by bending at the hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the resistance band with both hands, palms facing forward, and bring it up to shoulder level. | Step:3 Press the band overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the band back down to shoulder level. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, hanging towards the floor. | Step:2 Keep your arm straight and lift the dumbbell out to the side, away from your body. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and dumbbells in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the exercise ball until your lower back is supported on the ball and your knees are at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Shrug - Rigid Variation
instructions: Step:1 Set up a decline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 (rigid variation) Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended towards the floor. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, raise your shoulders towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Incline Press With Rigid
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench facing away from the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with one hand and bring it up to shoulder height. Emphasize rigid control. | Step:4 Position your feet firmly on the ground and maintain a stable position. | Step:5 Press the handle forward and upward, extending your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:2 Engage your core and press the dumbbell straight up overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to shoulder level. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Ez Barbell Decline Close Grip Face Press - Mini Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with a close grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up above your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then press the barbell back up to the starting position. Emphasize mini control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Traditional Barbell Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body. | Step:5 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the barbell. | Step:6 Once you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, push your hips forward and stand up straight. | Step:7 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:8 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on traditional movement.

name: Kettlebell Arnold Press - Beginner Variation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing towards you. | Step:2 Engage your core and press the kettlebells overhead, rotating your palms to face forward as you extend your arms. Emphasize beginner control. | Step:3 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the kettlebells back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Deep Smith Machine Reverse Decline Close Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. Focus on deep movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upright Smith Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 30-45 degree incline. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back flat against the pad and feet firmly on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Perform with upright intensity. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your upper chest, keeping your elbows slightly tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Fly On Exercise Ball Improved
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your upper back is resting on the exercise ball. | Step:3 Extend your arm with the dumbbell straight up above your chest, palm facing inwards. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms. Focus on improved movement.

name: Fast Band Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your feet. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands, palms facing your body, and keep your arms straight. | Step:3 Engage your core and maintain a slight bend in your knees. | Step:4 Slowly hinge forward at your hips, keeping your back straight and chest lifted. | Step:5 Lower the band towards the ground while keeping your legs straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then squeeze your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Perform with fast intensity.

name: Cable Lateral Pulldown (With Rope Attachment) Core
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to the cable machine at a high position. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Emphasize core control. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the tension and allow the rope to return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Around Pullover - Intensive Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet firmly on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight above your chest. Perform with intensive intensity. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head in an arc motion. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squared Reverse Grip Machine Lat Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest out and shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the handles down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Maintain squared form throughout. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Seated Press With High
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead, fully extending your arms. Focus on high movement. | Step:4 Lower the kettlebells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squat (On Knees) With Pure
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your shoulders, gripping it with an overhand grip and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you slowly lower your body down by bending your knees, keeping your back straight. Perform with pure intensity. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Tough Cable One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with one hand, palm facing down, and stand far enough away from the machine so that there is tension on the cable. | Step:3 Keep your arm straight and slowly raise it out to the side until it is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. Focus on tough movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Intensified Style Kettlebell Extended Range One Arm Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in one hand, with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow locked and your wrist straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm. Perform with intensified intensity.

name: Band Vertical Pallof Press - Seated Variation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and wrap the band around a sturdy object at chest height. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands and step away from the anchor point, creating tension in the band. | Step:3 Position yourself perpendicular to the anchor point, with your side facing the band. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, keeping your hands at chest height. | Step:5 Engage your core and press the band away from your chest, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Hold the position for a few seconds, then slowly bring the band back towards your chest. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides. Perform with seated intensity.

name: Barbell Reverse Wrist Curl - Prone Variation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the barbell towards your body. Emphasize prone control. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press On Exercise Ball With Extended
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand, feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. Perform with extended intensity. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell at shoulder height with your palm facing forward. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Lunge With Firm
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your chest up as you lower your body. Maintain firm form throughout. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45В° Leg Wide Press - Blunt Variation
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the foot platform. | Step:3 Position your feet wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push against the foot platform to extend your legs and straighten your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bend your knees to return to the starting position. Maintain blunt form throughout. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone Dumbbell Upright Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping your elbows slightly bent. Emphasize prone control. | Step:3 Rotate your arms externally, bringing the dumbbells up towards your head while keeping your elbows in the same position. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted One Hand Pull Up Fast
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arm fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbow and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 (fast variation) Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Targeted Style Smith Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. Focus on targeted movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Judo Flip With Static
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands at chest level, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and rotate your torso to the right, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 As you rotate, pivot your back foot and allow your hips to rotate naturally. Emphasize static control. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully and finish the movement by flipping the cable handle over your shoulder. | Step:6 Return to the starting position by reversing the movement, rotating your torso back to the center. | Step:7 Repeat the movement on the opposite side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Wrist Curl - Strength Variation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on the bench with your wrist hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrist upwards, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. Maintain strength form throughout. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Micro Style Barbell Speed Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips back and down, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 (micro variation) Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rough Cable Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the handles with your palms facing forward and your arms extended straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. Perform with rough intensity. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Bench Press Seated
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 (seated variation) Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Pull-Up Inclined
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height settings. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended and your feet off the ground. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the handles, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the handles. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain inclined form throughout.

name: Barbell Sitted Alternate Leg Raise (Female) With Intermediate
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and hold a barbell across your thighs. | Step:2 (intermediate variation) Place your hands on the sides of the bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, lift one leg up as high as possible while keeping it parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Lower the leg back down and repeat with the other leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Hammer Grip Deep
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place one foot on a raised surface, such as a step or block, with your heel hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with a hammer grip, meaning your palms are facing each other and your fingers are wrapped around the handle. | Step:4 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 (deep variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Gentle Style Cable Pulldown (Pro Lat Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your thighs are parallel to the ground and your feet are flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the lat bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and lean back slightly, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Maintain gentle form throughout. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell High Bar Squat Core
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Place the barbell on your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to squat down, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Perform with core intensity. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sharp Style Dumbbell Sumo Pull Through
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointed outwards. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands in front of your body, arms extended. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips down into a squat position, keeping your back straight. Focus on sharp movement. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell down between your legs, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Drive through your heels and extend your hips forward, pulling the dumbbell up and in front of your body. | Step:6 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, then lower the dumbbell back down between your legs. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Single Smith Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 (single variation) Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the bar off the rack and position it at shoulder level, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:4 Press the bar upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Behind Neck Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell behind your neck with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms, fully extending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lateral Pulldown With V-Bar
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the cable pulldown machine and grab the v-bar attachment with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Adjust the knee pad so that your thighs are secured under it. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the v-bar down towards your upper chest while keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your back muscles at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly return the v-bar to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Arm Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet planted firmly on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head in an arc-like motion. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Wide-Grip Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a wide grip and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the barbell behind your head in a controlled manner, keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Full Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Step under the bar and position it across your upper back, resting on your traps. | Step:4 Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Unrack the bar and take a step back, maintaining a stable stance. | Step:6 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, initiate the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:7 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as your flexibility allows. | Step:8 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then drive through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Decline Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and a barbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place the balls of your feet on a raised platform, such as a block or step. | Step:3 Position the barbell across your thighs and hold it securely with your hands. | Step:4 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, lift your heels off the ground by extending your ankles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your feet. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands, palms facing your body, and keep your arms straight. | Step:3 Engage your core and maintain a slight bend in your knees. | Step:4 Slowly hinge forward at your hips, keeping your back straight and chest lifted. | Step:5 Lower the band towards the ground while keeping your legs straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then squeeze your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Over Alternate Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Extend one arm straight back, keeping it close to your body, until your arm is fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Chest Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward, rolling the ball until your upper back is supported on the ball and your head, neck, and shoulders are off the ball. | Step:3 Extend your arm with the dumbbell straight up above your chest, palm facing inward. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Engage your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Band Kneeling One Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point above your head. | Step:2 Kneel down and hold the band with one hand, palm facing down. | Step:3 Extend your arm fully overhead, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Engage your lat muscles and pull the band down towards your side, bringing your elbow towards your ribcage. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Palm In Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height with your palm facing inwards. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Press the dumbbell upwards until your arm is fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Smith Machine Reverse Decline Close Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted One Hand Pull Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arm fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbow and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Fly (With Support)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing inwards. | Step:3 Lean forward and place your free hand on the bench for support. | Step:4 Keep your arm slightly bent and raise it out to the side until it is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball With Leg Raised
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 While performing the bicep curl, raise one leg off the ground and hold it in the air for the duration of the exercise. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Cable Standing Back Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your arms straight and your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the cable handle towards your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Palms In Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the backrest and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing inwards. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight up above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells slowly towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then press the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your chest up as you lower your body. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Y-Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Lean forward slightly and let your arms hang straight down, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides and up in a Y shape until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Bar Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable pulley to a high position and attach a straight bar. | Step:2 Sit facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back slightly and keep your chest up, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:5 Pull the bar down towards your chest, leading with your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Bent V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Slowly bend your torso to the right side, lowering the barbell towards your right knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement on the left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Lying One Hand Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and your head supported by your arm. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your top hand with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your arm straight, raise the dumbbell up to shoulder height. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Sled 45 Degrees One Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the footplate. | Step:3 Place one foot on the footplate and extend your leg, pushing the sled away from you. | Step:4 Slowly bend your knee and lower the sled back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Lying Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable weight. | Step:2 Lie on your back on the sled machine with your feet on the footplate. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly angled outwards. | Step:4 Grip the handles of the sled machine for stability. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:6 Push through your heels and extend your legs to lift the sled. | Step:7 Lower the sled back down by bending your knees and hips. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Behind Head Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and bring it down to shoulder level, behind your head. | Step:4 Press the barbell upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Military Press
