instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Rotate your arms so that your palms are facing downwards. | Step:5 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the cable handle in front of you, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Lift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and position it at waist height. | Step:3 Engage your core and maintain a straight back throughout the exercise. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the cable handle up towards your opposite shoulder, rotating your torso. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Smith Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Contralateral Forward Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending both knees until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Press Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a mat with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, resting it on your chest. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Finger Curls
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your forearm on your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Allow the dumbbell to roll down to your fingertips, then curl it back up by flexing your fingers. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Band Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your ankles. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and slowly lower your upper body towards the ground. | Step:4 As you lower, push your hips back and allow your knees to bend slightly. | Step:5 Lower the band towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your upper body back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Goblet Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, lower your body down into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Up Straight Crossovers
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the handles of the cables with your palms facing down and your arms extended straight out to the sides. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, bring your hands together in front of your body, crossing them over each other. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position, keeping your arms extended. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing your torso to lean forward. | Step:3 Continue lowering the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat (Back Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Raise And Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and raise the barbell in front of you until it reaches shoulder height. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Next, lower the barbell behind your head, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your forearms resting on your thighs, holding a barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Allow the barbell to roll down to your fingertips, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:3 Slowly curl the barbell up towards your forearms by flexing your wrists. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Palm Up
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place it on top of your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Lift one leg off the ground and extend it in front of you, keeping your knee slightly bent. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Cable Standing Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your arm extended in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow slightly bent and your shoulder blades pulled back. | Step:4 Slowly rotate your arm outward, away from your body, while keeping your elbow in the same position. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying External Shoulder Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side on a flat bench with your upper arm against your side and your elbow bent 90 degrees. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your hand with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm against your side, slowly rotate your forearm upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Reverse Grip Machine Lat Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest out and shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the handles down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell High Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Place the barbell on your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to squat down, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the high pulley of a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Engage your lats and pull the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wrist Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the barbell towards your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez-Bar Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45В° Leg Wide Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the foot platform. | Step:3 Position your feet wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push against the foot platform to extend your legs and straighten your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bend your knees to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:2 Place a barbell on the ground in front of you, centered between your feet. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, to grip the barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:4 Engage your core and drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees simultaneously. | Step:5 As you lift, keep your chest up and back straight, and push your hips forward to fully engage your glutes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows bent, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Twisting Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your side facing the anchor point and grab the band with one hand. | Step:3 Step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly bend your knees. | Step:5 Bring your hand holding the band across your body, towards the opposite shoulder. | Step:6 While maintaining tension in the band, push your hand forward and away from your body, extending your arm. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other hand.

name: Dumbbell Lateral To Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Next, raise your arms in front of you until they are parallel to the ground, again keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:2 Lean forward and position your upper arm against the inside of your thigh. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm slightly bent and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Seated Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells in front of you, with your palms facing down, until they are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead in a straight line, fully extending your arm. | Step:4 As you press the kettlebell overhead, simultaneously dip your knees and quickly straighten them to generate momentum. | Step:5 As the kettlebell reaches its highest point, quickly drop underneath it by bending your knees and hips. | Step:6 Catch the kettlebell with a slight bend in your knees and hips, and your arm fully extended overhead. | Step:7 Stand up straight, fully extending your knees and hips, and stabilize the kettlebell overhead. | Step:8 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position by bending your knees and hips, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pulldown (Pro Lat Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your thighs are parallel to the ground and your feet are flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the lat bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and lean back slightly, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twist (Up-Down)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips and legs stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the rotation to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Shoulder Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest of the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles of the machine with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push the handles upward and forward until your arms are fully extended, but not locked. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbells at shoulder level, elbows bent and pointing out to the sides. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells up and slightly inward, keeping your palms facing each other. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down in front of you, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Twist Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbells, twist your wrists so that your palms face forward at the bottom of the movement. | Step:5 Reverse the motion and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position, squeezing your chest muscles at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Close-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Using your thighs to help raise the dumbbells, lift the dumbbells one at a time so that you can hold them in front of you at shoulder width. | Step:3 Once at shoulder width, rotate your wrists forward so that the palms of your hands are facing away from you. This will be your starting position. | Step:4 As you breathe in, slowly lower the dumbbells to your side until they are about level with your chest. | Step:5 As you exhale, use your triceps to lift the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickbacks On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Twisted Flyes
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and press the dumbbells up to the starting position, directly above your chest, with your arms extended. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbells, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward at the bottom of the movement. | Step:5 Reverse the motion and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position, squeezing your chest muscles together at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Carry
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you walk forward, maintaining the dumbbell overhead. | Step:4 Continue walking for the desired distance or time. | Step:5 Switch hands and repeat the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Full Can Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Double Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand. | Step:2 Extend your right arm overhead, keeping your eyes on the kettlebell. | Step:3 Rotate your left foot 45 degrees to the left and your right foot 90 degrees to the right. | Step:4 Bend at the waist to the left, keeping your right arm extended overhead. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell towards the ground, reaching towards your left foot. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then engage your core and push through your right foot to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Horizontal Pallof Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand perpendicular to the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band handle with both hands and step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Bring your hands to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body. | Step:5 Engage your core and maintain a stable stance. | Step:6 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, pushing the band away from your body. | Step:7 Hold the extended position for a few seconds, focusing on maintaining tension in your core. | Step:8 Slowly bring your hands back to your chest, resisting the pull of the band. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest, close to your body. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips down and back, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine Inner Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Close Grip Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly closer than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lift the barbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Press the barbell overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body, arms extended downwards. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and knees, lowering the dumbbells towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Push through your heels and extend your hips and knees, lifting the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Twisting Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing away from you. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 As you lower the dumbbells, twist your wrists so that your palms face towards you at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then reverse the movement by pressing the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:7 As you press the dumbbells up, twist your wrists back to the starting position with palms facing away from you. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head, feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return the barbell to the starting position by reversing the motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Waiter Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms close to your body and your elbows tucked in. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Extension Pullover (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine and set the pulley at the highest position. | Step:2 Lie down on a bench with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, slowly lower the rope behind your head while maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise the rope back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells to your sides with a slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your chest up. | Step:3 Slowly hinge forward at the hips, lowering your torso towards the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Horizontal Dumbbell Standing Alternate Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 (horizontal variation) Press one dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder level. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Sumo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at hip height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper back and shoulders. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest out and shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the handles down towards your chest, leading with your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the resistance band handles in each hand, with your palms facing down and elbows bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arms forward, pushing the resistance band away from your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Bent Arm Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the barbell behind your head in a controlled manner, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position by contracting your lats. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell resting on your upper chest, just below your collarbone. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your elbows up and your upper arms parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Palms Up Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover Hip Extension On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and the dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the exercise ball down your back until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your arms straight and maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 While keeping your arms extended, lift your hips off the ground, squeezing your glutes and engaging your core. | Step:7 Lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Underhand Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulldown bar is at a height above your head. | Step:2 Sit down on the seat and grab the pulldown bar with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to chest level. | Step:2 Lie flat on the bench with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:3 Grip the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the bar and lower it towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the bar touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the bar back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45В° Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and footplate of the sled machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grip the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push the footplate away from your body by extending your legs, keeping your heels on the footplate. | Step:5 Continue pushing until your legs are almost fully extended, but without locking your knees. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the footplate back towards your body by bending your knees. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Standing Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height settings. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your lats and biceps, and pull yourself up towards the handles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your back muscles. | Step:6 Slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Pirate Supper Legs
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise the kettlebell up to shoulder height, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Extend your arm fully overhead, straightening your elbow. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell back down to shoulder height, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Decline Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with one hand, palm facing down, and stand far enough away from the machine so that there is tension on the cable. | Step:3 Keep your arm straight and slowly raise it out to the side until it is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge Two Legs On Bench (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start by sitting on the edge of a bench with your upper back resting against it and your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles, then press through your heels to lift your hips off the bench, creating a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Rest your forearms on a bench or pad, with your wrists hanging off the edge. | Step:5 Keeping your forearms stationary, exhale and curl your wrists upward as far as possible. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a weight in front of your chest or on your shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips down and back, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Push through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Landmine Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, resting it on the front of your shoulders. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and back straight, lift the barbell up and away from your body, raising it to shoulder height. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Frankenstein Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell in front of your body with straight arms. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight, lower your body by bending at the knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Fixed Back Close Grip Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a fixed point above you, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy beam. | Step:2 Sit down on a bench or chair facing the band, with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:3 Grasp the band with a close grip, palms facing towards you. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the band down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lats. | Step:7 Slowly release the band back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twisting Pull
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and step away from the machine, extending your arm fully. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart, with your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your torso to the right as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position, keeping tension on the cable. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform with your right hand.

name: Cable Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend at the hips and knees, lowering your torso until your back is parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders back. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift the cable handles, extending your hips and standing up straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lunge With Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. Your right knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle and your left knee should be hovering just above the ground. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, simultaneously curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the lunge, then push through your right heel to return to the starting position, lowering the dumbbells back down to your sides. | Step:5 Repeat the lunge and bicep curl on the opposite side, stepping forward with your left foot. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Seated Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Lower the kettlebells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the barbell towards your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying flat on your back on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles, then lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your chest against the backrest and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down with your palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Alternate Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the handles of the cable machine with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Position your hands at shoulder height, with your palms facing forward. | Step:3 Keep your core engaged and your back straight. | Step:4 Press one handle up and forward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:7 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Wide Grip Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the decline bench to the desired angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows pointed outwards. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Revers Wrist Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:4 Keeping your forearms stationary, exhale and curl your wrists upward as far as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Lateral Bent-Over
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a cable machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with one hand and step back to create tension on the cable. | Step:3 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Extend your arm out to the side, parallel to the ground, with a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Overhead Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball and hold the cable handle with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your elbows close to your ears. | Step:3 Slowly curl the cable down towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, using your calves. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your thighs. | Step:2 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the dumbbells in front of you until they are at shoulder level. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Back Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body size and range of motion. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet secured. | Step:3 Place your hands on the handles or grip bars. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lean forward, allowing your back to round slightly. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom position, feeling a stretch in your lower back. | Step:6 Using your back muscles, slowly raise your torso back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Overhead Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your upper arms stationary and your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Exhale and curl the cable attachment towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the cable attachment back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down towards the ground, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lift your arms out to the sides and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low position and attach the handles. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height settings. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended and your feet off the ground. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the handles, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the handles. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 30-45 degree incline. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back flat against the pad and feet firmly on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your upper chest, keeping your elbows slightly tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Push Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and dip your body down, then explosively extend your legs and press the dumbbells overhead. | Step:3 Lock out your arms at the top of the movement, then lower the dumbbells back to shoulder level. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Floor Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the kettlebell in one hand with your palm facing towards your feet and your arm extended straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Slowly lower the kettlebell towards your chest by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment when the kettlebell is just above your chest, then push it back up to the starting position by extending your elbow. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Seated Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and cable handles to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip at shoulder height. | Step:4 Push the handles forward and away from your body, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Lifting (On Hip)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip and position it on your hips. | Step:3 Engaging your glutes, lift your hips off the bench until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bent Arm Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a shoulder-width grip and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the barbell behind your head while keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Bar Lying Bent Arms Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold the EZ barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return the barbell to the starting position by reversing the arc motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Arnold Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support and hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level, palms facing your body and elbows bent. | Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended and your palms are facing forward. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists as you lift, so that your palms are facing forward at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Sissy Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a weight in front of your chest with both hands, or place a barbell across your upper back. | Step:3 Keeping your chest up and your core engaged, slowly lower your body down by bending at the knees and hips. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Split Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outwards. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your shoulders. | Step:3 Take a big step to the side with your right foot, keeping your left foot planted. | Step:4 Bend your right knee and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping out with your left foot. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling your body down the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbells at shoulder level, elbows bent and pointing out to the sides. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells upward, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Bradford Rocky Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbows slightly bent and pointing forward. | Step:4 Press the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45° Leg Press (Side Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the sled machine so that your knees are at a 90-degree angle when your feet are on the footplate. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back flat against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grip the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push against the footplate to extend your legs, straightening them completely. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly bend your knees to lower the footplate back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and handles of the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and grasp the handles with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your arms slightly bent and your core engaged. | Step:4 Slowly pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your lats. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supination
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by contracting your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the decline bench to the desired angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Shoulder
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards, and raise them to shoulder height. | Step:3 Press one dumbbell up overhead while keeping the other dumbbell at shoulder height. | Step:4 Lower the raised dumbbell back to shoulder height while simultaneously pressing the other dumbbell up overhead. | Step:5 Continue alternating between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to chest level. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Step back and position yourself with a slight bend in your knees. | Step:5 Keep your chest up and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Lower the bar towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Sumo High Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell with both hands in front of your body, arms extended downwards. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips into a squat position, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Drive through your heels and explosively extend your hips and knees, pulling the kettlebell up towards your chin. | Step:5 As you pull the kettlebell up, keep your elbows high and wide, and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Neutral Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and your arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to chest height and attach the handles. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and step forward to create tension in the cables. | Step:4 Position your feet firmly on the ground and engage your core. | Step:5 Bend your elbows and bring your hands to shoulder level, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:6 Push the handles forward, extending your arms fully in front of you. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then slowly reverse the movement, bringing your hands back to shoulder level. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Plank With Rear Fly
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, keeping your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in your top hand, with your arm extended straight down towards the ground. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:5 While maintaining the side plank position, lift the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand, feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell at shoulder height with your palm facing forward. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and position the dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells up and away from your body until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Military Press To The Side
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight down towards the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Engaging your shoulder muscles, lift your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at an appropriate height for your squat. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper traps and shoulders. | Step:4 Grip the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and unrack the barbell, stepping back to clear the rack. | Step:6 Keeping your chest up and back straight, initiate the squat by bending at the hips and knees. | Step:7 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:8 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then drive through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Shoulder Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest the dumbbells on your thighs and lean back onto the bench. | Step:3 Use your thighs to help raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, then rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Exhale and slowly raise the dumbbells above your head, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your head, neck, and upper back are supported by the ball. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up above your chest, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Bend your elbows slightly and lower your arms out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then reverse the movement and squeeze your chest muscles as you bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows slightly flared out. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, bending at the knees and hips. | Step:4 As you lower, push your knees out to the sides and keep your weight on your heels. | Step:5 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Extended Range One Arm Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in one hand, with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow locked and your wrist straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Exercise Ball On The Wall Calf Raise (Tennis Ball Between Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and place an exercise ball between your lower back and the wall. | Step:2 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly in front of you. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms extended by your sides. | Step:4 Place a tennis ball between your knees. | Step:5 Raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squat Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Start with the barbell resting on your shoulders, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your chest up and your knees tracking over your toes. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the squat, explosively drive through your legs and push the barbell overhead. | Step:4 As the barbell reaches its peak, quickly drop into a split position, with one foot forward and one foot back. | Step:5 Catch the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended and your back knee slightly touching the ground. | Step:6 Stand up from the split position, bringing your feet back together. | Step:7 Lower the barbell back to your shoulders and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Elbow Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other and arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then press the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your elbows. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Decline Chest Fly
