instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to a low pulley cable machine and set the bench to a decline angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your head towards the machine and grab the handle with your right hand. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:4 With a controlled motion, lower your arm out to the side until your hand is in line with your shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then reverse the motion and bring your arm back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left arm and repeat the exercise.

name: Cable One Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip and extend your arm fully. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the handle down towards your side while keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your lat muscle. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Over Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your head up. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Incline Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench facing away from the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with one hand and bring it up to shoulder height. | Step:4 Position your feet firmly on the ground and maintain a stable position. | Step:5 Press the handle forward and upward, extending your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Full Maltese
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides. | Step:2 Slowly lean forward, keeping your arms straight, until your upper body is parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engage your core and hold this position for a few seconds. | Step:4 Return to the starting position by pushing through your feet and standing back up. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Diamond Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands close together, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers. | Step:2 Keep your body in a straight line from head to toe, engaging your core and glutes. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the diamond shape formed by your hands, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Forward Lunge (Male) With Bench
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hands on your hips. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Bend your right knee to about 90 degrees, keeping your knee aligned with your ankle. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and return to the starting position. Focus on bench movement. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternating Bear Crawl
instructions: Step:1 Start on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips. | Step:2 Lift your knees slightly off the ground, keeping your back flat and your core engaged. | Step:3 Move your right hand and left foot forward simultaneously, followed by your left hand and right foot. | Step:4 Continue crawling forward, alternating your hand and foot movements. | Step:5 Maintain a steady pace and keep your core tight throughout the exercise. | Step:6 (alternating variation) Continue for the desired distance or time.

name: High Knee Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your right knee up towards your chest, while keeping your left foot on the ground. | Step:4 Quickly switch legs, bringing your left knee up towards your chest and lowering your right foot back down. | Step:5 Continue alternating legs in a running motion, bringing your knees up as high as possible. | Step:6 Maintain a fast pace and keep your upper body stable throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Front Plank With Twist
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:2 Engage your core and glutes to maintain a stable position. | Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, lifting your right arm and extending it towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Keep your hips and legs stable as you twist. | Step:5 Hold for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the twist on the left side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pure Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. Emphasize pure control. | Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Plank With Leg Lift
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you and your hands resting on the ground behind you, fingers pointing towards your feet. | Step:2 Press through your hands and lift your hips off the ground, coming into a reverse plank position. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift one leg off the ground, extending it straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Hold for a moment, then lower your leg back down. | Step:5 Repeat with the other leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (Wall)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall, about arm's length away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back a few feet, keeping your body straight and your feet hip-width apart. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the wall, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:5 Push back up to the starting position, straightening your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Impossible Dips
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body suspended in the air. | Step:2 Bend your knees and cross your ankles. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rear Decline Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Place your arms by your sides with your palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, and lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push-Up (On Box) - Active Variation
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the edge of a box or elevated surface, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the box by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 (active variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Dip (Bench Leg)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward, sliding your butt off the bench, and straighten your arms. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Endurance Style One Arm Dip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a bench or chair, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place one hand on the bench or chair behind you, fingers pointing towards your body. Maintain endurance form throughout. | Step:3 Extend your legs out in front of you, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench or chair. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat with the other arm.

name: Arms Overhead Full Sit-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms overhead, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is upright. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cocoons With Mega
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Emphasize mega control.

name: Dead Bug
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended towards the ceiling. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your legs off the ground, creating a 90-degree angle at your hips and knees. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower back to press your lower back into the ground. | Step:4 Slowly lower your right arm and left leg towards the ground, keeping them straight and hovering just above the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement with your left arm and right leg. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rounded Twisted Leg Raise (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your legs off the ground, bringing them towards your chest. Emphasize rounded control. | Step:3 As you lift your legs, twist your hips to one side, bringing your knees towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your hips to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide-Grip Chest Dip On High Parallel Bars - Low Variation
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body suspended in the air. | Step:2 Lean forward slightly and lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest is just above the bars. | Step:3 (low variation) Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: High Style Scapula Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 As you lower, squeeze your shoulder blades together and push your chest forward. Focus on high movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Incline Side Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:5 Lower your hips back down to the ground and repeat on the other side.

name: Half Knee Bends (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body down as if you were sitting back into a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your weight in your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Low Glute Bridge On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your arms by your sides, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core, then lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up Inside Leg Kick
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 As you push back up, lift one leg off the ground and kick it out to the side, keeping it straight. | Step:4 Lower your leg back down and repeat the push-up, then switch to the other leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating leg kicks with each push-up repetition.

name: Hanging Pike With Intense
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up towards the bar, keeping them straight. | Step:3 (intense variation) Continue lifting until your body forms a 'V' shape, with your legs parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold the position for a moment, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spider Crawl Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Bring your right knee towards your right elbow, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 As you bring your right knee back, simultaneously lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position and repeat with your left knee towards your left elbow. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Hand Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Keep your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Abdominal Fallout - Inclined Variation
instructions: Step:1 Attach a suspension trainer to a high anchor point and adjust the straps to waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point and hold the handles with your arms extended in front of you. Maintain inclined form throughout. | Step:3 Lean forward at the waist, keeping your body straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Lower your body as far as you can while maintaining control and tension in your abs. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inclined Style Pelvic Tilt Into Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your arms by your sides with your palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:4 Tilt your pelvis upward, lifting your hips off the ground. Emphasize inclined control. | Step:5 Hold the bridge position for a few seconds. | Step:6 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elevator
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or cross them in front of your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly bend forward at the waist, lowering your upper body towards the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise your upper body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kick Out Sit
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Lean back slightly and place your hands on the edge of the bench or chair for support. | Step:3 Engaging your hamstrings, lift your feet off the ground and extend your legs straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly bend your knees and bring your feet back towards your body. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Clock Push-Up Extreme
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower, rotate your body to the left, extending your left arm straight out to the side. Focus on extreme movement. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position, while rotating your body to the center. | Step:5 Repeat the push-up, this time rotating your body to the right and extending your right arm out to the side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides with each repetition.

name: Outside Leg Kick Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 As you push back up, kick one leg out to the side, extending it fully and engaging your glutes. | Step:4 Return your leg to the starting position and repeat the push-up, alternating legs with each repetition. | Step:5 Continue alternating leg kicks and push-ups for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upward Facing Dog
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with your legs extended behind you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the floor next to your lower ribs, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Press your hands firmly into the floor and straighten your arms, lifting your torso and thighs off the ground. | Step:4 Roll your shoulders back and down, opening your chest and lifting your gaze towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Hold this position for a few breaths, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Half Knee Bends (Male) With Blunt
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body down as if you were sitting back into a chair. Emphasize blunt control. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your weight in your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bench Dip (Knees Bent)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench and straighten your legs in front of you, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips. | Step:2 Shift your weight to one leg and lift the opposite leg out to the side, keeping it straight. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Glute-Ham Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the glute-ham raise machine to fit your body. | Step:2 Position yourself face down on the machine with your ankles secured. | Step:3 Place your hands on your chest or cross them over your chest. | Step:4 Engage your hamstrings and glutes to lift your upper body up towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Continue lifting until your body is in a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Front Lever Reps
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 Keeping your body straight, lift your legs up until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for as long as you can, aiming for 10-20 seconds. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Swing 360
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engage your core and swing your arms in a circular motion, rotating your torso as you do so. | Step:4 Continue the circular motion, swinging your arms and rotating your torso for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:5 Remember to breathe throughout the exercise.

name: Quick Feet V. 2 With Bent
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Begin by rapidly moving your feet up and down, as if you were running in place. | Step:3 Keep your movements quick and light, focusing on staying on the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions. Emphasize bent control.

name: Hip Raise (Bent Knee)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Straddle Maltese
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pair of rings with your arms fully extended and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Spread your legs wide apart, forming a straddle position. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lower your body until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Pike Weak
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up towards the bar, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your body forms a 'V' shape, with your legs parallel to the ground. Emphasize weak control. | Step:4 Hold the position for a moment, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twist Hip Lift
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 While keeping your hips lifted, twist your lower body to the right side, bringing your knees towards the ground. | Step:5 Return to the starting position and repeat the twist to the left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Improved Sphinx
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the ground with your forearms flat on the floor, elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest off the ground, keeping your forearms and toes on the floor. | Step:3 Hold this position for a few seconds, making sure to keep your neck in a neutral position. | Step:4 Slowly lower your chest back down to the starting position. Emphasize improved control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Isometric Wipers
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying flat on your back on a mat or bench. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, perpendicular to your body. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift both legs off the ground, keeping them together and straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower your legs to one side, aiming to touch the ground with your feet while maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then use your core to lift your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, this time lowering your legs to the opposite side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Arms Apart Circular Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Keeping your legs straight, bend forward at the waist and reach down towards your toes with your right hand. | Step:3 As you reach down, simultaneously lift your left leg straight up behind you, maintaining balance. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left hand reaching towards your toes and your right leg lifting up behind you. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Gorilla Chin
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:4 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, bringing your chin above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Quads Complex
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back as if sitting on a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Push through your heels to return to the starting position. Emphasize complex control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Scapula Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Position your feet on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:4 Lower your chest towards the bench, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 As you lower, retract your shoulder blades, squeezing your scapulae together. | Step:6 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip On Straight Bar
instructions: Step:1 Grab the parallel bars with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Bend your knees and cross your ankles. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your arms until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:3 Pause for a moment when your chest is just above the ground, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Twisting Leg Hip Raise With Compound
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your legs straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up towards your chest, keeping them straight. Perform with compound intensity. | Step:3 Once your legs are parallel to the ground, twist your hips to one side, bringing your legs towards that side. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, but this time twist your hips to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Basic Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Reach down towards your toes with your hands, keeping your legs as straight as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands placed close together, directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your bottom hand on the ground directly under your shoulder, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Press through your bottom hand to lift your body off the ground, keeping your legs straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Extend your top arm straight up towards the ceiling, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:5 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: One Arm Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out in front of you and place your palm against the wall. | Step:3 Engage your core and lean your body forward, keeping your arm straight and your back flat. | Step:4 Slowly push against the wall with your palm, activating your lat muscles. | Step:5 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and repeat with the other arm.

name: Hug Keens To Chest
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat position. | Step:3 As you squat down, bring your knees up towards your chest and hug them with your arms. | Step:4 Hold this position for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flag
instructions: Step:1 Start by gripping a vertical pole with both hands, palms facing each other, and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Using your core and upper body strength, raise your legs until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for as long as you can, maintaining a straight body line. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kipping Muscle Up With Triple
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and use a swinging motion to generate momentum. | Step:3 As you swing forward, pull your chest towards the bar, using your lats and biceps to initiate the movement. Emphasize triple control. | Step:4 Continue the upward motion until your chest reaches the bar, then transition into a dip position by pushing down on the bar and extending your arms. | Step:5 Lower yourself back down to the starting position by bending your arms and controlling the descent. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intermediate Style Kneeling Plank Tap Shoulder (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a kneeling position with your hands on the ground, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on your toes, and lift your body into a plank position. | Step:3 (intermediate variation) Keeping your core engaged and your hips stable, lift one hand off the ground and tap the opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Return the hand to the ground and repeat with the other hand. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Modified Push Up To Lower Arms
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your body down towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Once your elbows are at a 90-degree angle, lower your forearms to the ground, keeping your elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your palms to lift your forearms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side-To-Side Chin With Reverse
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body relaxed. | Step:4 Pull yourself up by bending your elbows and bringing your chin towards the bar, while keeping your body straight. Perform with reverse intensity. | Step:5 Once your chin is above the bar, lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Macro Style Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands placed close together, directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Maintain macro form throughout. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Janda Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bench Dip On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent Knee Lying Twist (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms out to the sides, perpendicular to your body. | Step:3 Keeping your knees together, slowly lower them to one side, aiming to touch the ground with your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then engage your core and slowly lift your knees back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Handstand
instructions: Step:1 Find an open space with enough room to perform a handstand. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Kick your legs up towards the wall, using your core and shoulders to maintain balance. | Step:4 Once in a handstand position, engage your triceps to support your body weight. | Step:5 Hold the handstand for as long as you can maintain balance. | Step:6 To come down, slowly lower your legs back to the ground. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up On Lower Arms - Resistance Variation
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your forearms on the ground and elbows directly below your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. Emphasize resistance control. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Full Planche Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, lean your body forward and lift your feet off the ground, balancing on your hands. | Step:4 Continue to lower your body until your chest is just above the ground. | Step:5 Push through your hands and extend your arms to lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Maintain a straight line from your head to your heels throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Dip (Between Benches)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge of the bench, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Clock Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower, rotate your body to the left, extending your left arm straight out to the side. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position, while rotating your body to the center. | Step:5 Repeat the push-up, this time rotating your body to the right and extending your right arm out to the side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides with each repetition.

name: Seated Wide Angle Pose Sequence
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in a wide angle. | Step:2 Flex your feet and engage your quadriceps. | Step:3 Place your hands on the ground behind you for support. | Step:4 Keeping your back straight, lean forward from your hips. | Step:5 Continue leaning forward until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:6 Hold this position for a few breaths. | Step:7 Slowly release the stretch and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side-To-Side Chin
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body relaxed. | Step:4 Pull yourself up by bending your elbows and bringing your chin towards the bar, while keeping your body straight. | Step:5 Once your chin is above the bar, lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sphinx
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the ground with your forearms flat on the floor, elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest off the ground, keeping your forearms and toes on the floor. | Step:3 Hold this position for a few seconds, making sure to keep your neck in a neutral position. | Step:4 Slowly lower your chest back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (Wall) With Static
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall, about arm's length away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back a few feet, keeping your body straight and your feet hip-width apart. | Step:4 (static variation) Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the wall, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:5 Push back up to the starting position, straightening your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Fierce Style Forward Lunge (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hands on your hips. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Bend your right knee to about 90 degrees, keeping your knee aligned with your ankle. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and return to the starting position. | Step:5 (fierce variation) Repeat with your left leg, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin-Up Diagonal
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 (diagonal variation) Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up Plus
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Once your chest is just above the ground, push through your hands to extend your arms and lift your upper body up. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, protract your shoulder blades by pushing your upper back towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then reverse the movement by retracting your shoulder blades and lowering your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Dip (Between Benches) - Extreme Variation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge of the bench, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 (extreme variation) Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Front Lever
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 Bend your knees and tuck them towards your chest. | Step:4 Simultaneously, lift your legs up and extend them straight out in front of you, keeping your body parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Hold this position for as long as you can, aiming for a full front lever position. | Step:6 To release, slowly lower your legs back down and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Drop Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Once your chest is just above the ground, quickly drop your knees to the ground. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twisted Side-To-Side Chin
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body relaxed. | Step:4 Pull yourself up by bending your elbows and bringing your chin towards the bar, while keeping your body straight. | Step:5 Once your chin is above the bar, lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Perform with twisted intensity.

name: Decline Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your knees bent. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the bench, curling forward towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bottoms-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring them towards your chest, keeping your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your hips off the ground, bringing your knees towards your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Two Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Reach down towards your toes with both hands, keeping your legs straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up To Side Plank - Athletic Variation
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your core engaged. | Step:3 Push back up to the starting position. Emphasize athletic control. | Step:4 Shift your weight onto your left hand and rotate your body to the right, lifting your right arm towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Hold the side plank position for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and side plank on the opposite side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twisted Leg Raise (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your legs off the ground, bringing them towards your chest. | Step:3 As you lift your legs, twist your hips to one side, bringing your knees towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your hips to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Find a suspension trainer and adjust it to an appropriate height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point and hold the handles with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Walk your feet forward, leaning your body forward until your weight is supported by the suspension trainer. | Step:4 Keep your body straight from head to heels, engage your core, and lower your chest towards the handles. | Step:5 Push through your chest and arms to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crab Twist Toe Touch
instructions: Step:1 Start by sitting on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Place your hands behind you, fingers pointing towards your feet, and lift your hips off the ground. | Step:3 Extend one leg straight out in front of you while simultaneously reaching your opposite hand towards your toes. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Mixed Grip Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an underhand grip (palms facing towards you) and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spine Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:4 Engage your abs and slowly twist your torso to the right, bringing your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the twist to the left side, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Reverse Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the edge of a bench or elevated surface, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the bench by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide-Grip Chest Dip On High Parallel Bars
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body suspended in the air. | Step:2 Lean forward slightly and lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest is just above the bars. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Leg Floor Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place your hands on a wall or sturdy object for balance. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel off the ground, lifting your body up onto the ball of your foot. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Elbow Lift - Reverse Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on the ground with your legs extended and your hands placed directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and press through your palms to lift your upper body off the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Pause at the top for a moment, squeezing your upper back muscles. | Step:4 Slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Arm Dip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a bench or chair, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place one hand on the bench or chair behind you, fingers pointing towards your body. | Step:3 Extend your legs out in front of you, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench or chair. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat with the other arm.

name: Plyo Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:3 Push explosively off the ground, using your chest muscles to propel your upper body off the ground. | Step:4 Land softly with your hands back in the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Abdominal Fallout
instructions: Step:1 Attach a suspension trainer to a high anchor point and adjust the straps to waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point and hold the handles with your arms extended in front of you. | Step:3 Lean forward at the waist, keeping your body straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Lower your body as far as you can while maintaining control and tension in your abs. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunge With Twist
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 As you lunge, twist your torso to the right, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, stepping forward with your left foot and twisting your torso to the left. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Calves
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, standing on your toes. | Step:3 Hold the position for a moment, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Archer
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, keeping your arms extended and your back straight. | Step:4 As you rotate, extend your right arm forward and your left arm back, mimicking the motion of drawing a bowstring. | Step:5 Hold the position for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the motion, this time rotating your torso to the left and extending your left arm forward and your right arm back. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Bridge Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Prop yourself up on your forearm, keeping your elbow directly below your shoulder. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 While keeping your core engaged, lift your top leg as high as possible without rotating your hips. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then lower your leg back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Quick Feet V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Begin by rapidly moving your feet up and down, as if you were running in place. | Step:3 Keep your movements quick and light, focusing on staying on the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Kipping Muscle Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and use a swinging motion to generate momentum. | Step:3 As you swing forward, pull your chest towards the bar, using your lats and biceps to initiate the movement. | Step:4 Continue the upward motion until your chest reaches the bar, then transition into a dip position by pushing down on the bar and extending your arms. | Step:5 Lower yourself back down to the starting position by bending your arms and controlling the descent. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Body-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by placing your hands on a raised surface, such as a bench or parallel bars, with your palms facing down and fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Extend your legs out in front of you, keeping your heels on the ground and your body straight. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides, until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your palms to straighten your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Korean Dips
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your arms extended and supporting your body weight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Tap Push-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, tap your chest with your right hand. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, this time tapping your chest with your left hand. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Dip
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shoulder Tap Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 As you push back up, lift your right hand off the ground and tap your left shoulder. | Step:4 Return your right hand to the ground and repeat the push-up, this time lifting your left hand and tapping your right shoulder. | Step:5 Continue alternating shoulder taps with each push-up repetition. | Step:6 Maintain a stable core and avoid excessive hip rotation throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Forward Lunge (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hands on your hips. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Bend your right knee to about 90 degrees, keeping your knee aligned with your ankle. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Dip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Full Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly shift your weight forward, lifting your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Continue shifting your weight forward until your body is parallel to the ground, balancing on your hands. | Step:4 Hold this position for as long as you can, maintaining a straight body line. | Step:5 Slowly lower your feet back to the ground and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Twisting Leg Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your legs straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up towards your chest, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Once your legs are parallel to the ground, twist your hips to one side, bringing your legs towards that side. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, but this time twist your hips to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cocoons
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, with your body forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the elevated surface by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking High Knees Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Lift your right knee up towards your chest as high as you can while balancing on your left leg. | Step:3 Step forward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position, bending both knees to a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and bring your left knee up towards your chest. | Step:5 Step forward with your left foot and lower your body into a lunge position. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs and lunging forward, keeping your core engaged and maintaining a steady pace. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Frog Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 As you lower your body, lift your feet off the ground and bring your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then extend your legs back out and push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Hyper On Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with your hips at the edge and your legs hanging off the bench. | Step:2 Hold onto the bench for stability. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, raise them up towards the ceiling as high as you can. | Step:4 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Arm Slingers Hanging Straight Legs
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your legs straight down. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Hold for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Butt-Ups
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, squeeze your abs and pause for a moment. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: March Sit (Wall)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Slowly slide your back down the wall until your knees are bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Lift your right foot off the ground and bring your knee towards your chest. | Step:4 Lower your right foot back down and lift your left foot off the ground, bringing your knee towards your chest. | Step:5 Continue alternating between lifting your right and left foot for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Leg Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up by flexing your hips and knees until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lean Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly shift your weight forward, bringing your shoulders past your hands. | Step:3 Keep your elbows slightly bent and your body straight as you lean forward. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wrist Circles
instructions: Step:1 Extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Make a fist with both hands. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists in a circular motion, keeping your arms still. | Step:4 Continue the wrist circles for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Leg Donkey Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place your hands on a stable surface for support, such as a wall or a bar. | Step:3 Lift one leg off the ground, keeping your knee slightly bent. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Hands Reversed Clasped Circular Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Reach down with your hands and clasp them together behind your legs. | Step:4 Slowly raise your hands up and over your head in a circular motion, keeping your legs straight. | Step:5 Continue the circular motion until your hands touch your toes. | Step:6 Reverse the motion and bring your hands back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shoulder Tap
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your right hand off the ground, reaching across to tap your left shoulder. | Step:3 Place your right hand back on the ground and repeat with your left hand tapping your right shoulder. | Step:4 Continue alternating shoulder taps while keeping your hips and torso stable. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up (On Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Start by getting on your hands and knees, with your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your upper body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Pause for a moment when your chest is just above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Power Point Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your glutes to maintain a stable position. | Step:3 Lower your body down onto your forearms, one arm at a time, maintaining a straight line from head to toe. | Step:4 Hold this position for the desired amount of time, keeping your core and glutes engaged. | Step:5 To return to the starting position, push through your forearms and lift your body back up into a high plank position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Monster Walk
instructions: Step:1 Place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly bend your knees. | Step:3 Take a step to the side with your right foot, maintaining tension on the resistance band. | Step:4 Follow with your left foot, stepping to the side to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Bodyweight Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place your hands on a wall or stable surface for balance. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Bridge V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:5 Lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side.

name: One Arm Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a pull-up bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an underhand grip, with one hand gripping the bar and the other hand holding your wrist for support. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arm fully extended, keeping your body straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull yourself up towards the bar by bending your elbow and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Arm Slingers Hanging Bent Knee Legs
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest, bringing them as close to your elbows as possible. | Step:3 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:3 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Calf Raise (On A Staircase)
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a step or a sturdy platform with your heels hanging off and your toes on the step. | Step:2 Hold onto a railing or wall for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Elbow To Knee
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the ground, bringing your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:4 At the same time, extend your right leg straight out and lift it off the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, this time bringing your left elbow towards your right knee and extending your left leg. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pelvic Tilt Into Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your arms by your sides with your palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:4 Tilt your pelvis upward, lifting your hips off the ground. | Step:5 Hold the bridge position for a few seconds. | Step:6 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: 3/4 Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flexion Leg Sit Up (Straight Arm)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and arms straight above your head. | Step:2 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground while simultaneously lifting your legs towards your chest. | Step:3 Reach your hands towards your toes as you lift your upper body and legs. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body and legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inchworm
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist and place your hands on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Walk your hands forward until you are in a high plank position, with your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then walk your hands back towards your feet, keeping your legs as straight as possible. | Step:5 Once your hands reach your feet, stand back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Hip (On Parallel Bars)
instructions: Step:1 Stand between two parallel bars with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bars and lift your body off the ground, supporting your weight on your arms. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly lift your legs to the side, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pike-To-Cobra Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, forming an inverted V shape with your body. | Step:3 Lower your upper body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 As you lower down, shift your weight forward and transition into a cobra pose by straightening your arms and lifting your chest up. | Step:5 Reverse the movement by bending your elbows and lowering your chest back down towards the ground. | Step:6 Push through your hands to return to the inverted V position. | Step:7 Continue the movement by lowering your hips back down towards the ground, returning to the starting push-up position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking Lunge
