instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right leg, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Keep your torso upright and your front knee aligned with your ankle. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and bring your left foot forward, stepping into a lunge position with your left leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating legs and walking forward, maintaining a controlled and steady pace. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Muscle Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 As you reach the top of the movement, transition your grip so that your palms are facing towards you. | Step:4 Continue pulling yourself up until your chest is above the bar and your arms are fully flexed. | Step:5 Reverse the movement by slowly lowering yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Raise Single Arm Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out to the side, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position, using your chest muscles to lift your body. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm extended.

name: Inchworm V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist and place your hands on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Walk your hands forward until you are in a high plank position, with your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:4 Keeping your legs straight, walk your feet towards your hands, bringing your hips up towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Continue walking your hands forward, repeating the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling Plank Tap Shoulder (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a kneeling position with your hands on the ground, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on your toes, and lift your body into a plank position. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and your hips stable, lift one hand off the ground and tap the opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Return the hand to the ground and repeat with the other hand. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Handstand Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Find a wall and face away from it, standing a few feet away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground shoulder-width apart and kick your feet up against the wall, coming into a handstand position. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your head towards the ground, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Push through your hands and extend your arms to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Glute Bridge March
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Engage your glutes and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:3 While keeping your hips lifted, lift one foot off the ground and bring your knee towards your chest. | Step:4 Lower your foot back to the ground and repeat the movement with the other leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating legs in a marching motion while maintaining the bridge position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Plank Hip Adduction
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Prop yourself up on your forearm, keeping your elbow directly below your shoulder. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 While maintaining the side plank position, lift your top leg towards the ceiling, keeping it straight. | Step:5 Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Straight Leg Outer Hip Abductor
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your bottom arm under your head for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your top leg as high as possible without rotating your hips or leaning backward. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Glute Bridge Two Legs On Bench (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your back against it and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, then lift your hips off the bench until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hands Clasped Circular Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands clasped together in front of your chest. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Lower your hands towards your toes in a circular motion, reaching as far as you can without straining. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Modified Hindu Push-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground, bending your elbows and keeping your core engaged. | Step:3 As you lower your body, shift your weight back and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, creating an inverted V shape with your body. | Step:4 Continue to lower your body until your chest is just above the ground, then reverse the movement, pushing your hips back down and extending your arms to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Skater Hops
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and jump to the right, landing on your right foot. | Step:3 As you land, swing your left leg behind your right leg and tap the ground with your left toes. | Step:4 Immediately jump to the left, landing on your left foot. | Step:5 As you land, swing your right leg behind your left leg and tap the ground with your right toes. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides, jumping and tapping the ground with each leg. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side-To-Side Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Bend at the waist to the right, reaching your right hand towards your right foot while keeping your left hand extended to the side. | Step:3 Return to the starting position and then bend at the waist to the left, reaching your left hand towards your left foot while keeping your right hand extended to the side. | Step:4 Repeat the side-to-side bending motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Left Hook. Boxing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Keep your left hand up to protect your face and your right hand by your chin. | Step:3 Rotate your hips and pivot on your left foot as you extend your left arm forward in a punching motion. | Step:4 Twist your torso and engage your core muscles to generate power in the punch. | Step:5 Snap your arm back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Straddle Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet spread wide apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly shift your weight forward, bringing your shoulders over your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Swimmer Kicks V. 2 (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat with your arms extended overhead. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest and legs off the ground simultaneously. | Step:3 Kick your legs up and down in a fluttering motion, as if you were swimming. | Step:4 Continue kicking for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:5 Lower your chest and legs back down to the starting position.

name: Muscle-Up (On Vertical Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a vertical bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 As you pull yourself up, lean back slightly and bring your elbows towards your sides. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chest reaches the bar and your elbows are fully bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ring Dips
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from the rings with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:3 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up On Lower Arms
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your forearms on the ground and elbows directly below your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Quads
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back as if sitting on a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your hips forward off the bench and straighten your legs, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Archer Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out to the side, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, extending the opposite arm out to the side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (Wall) V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall, about arm's length away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back with your feet, keeping them hip-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:5 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the wall, keeping your body straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Close Grip Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twisted Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift both legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:4 As you lift your legs, twist your hips to one side, bringing your legs towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your hips to the other side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flutter Kicks
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your hands by your sides. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground about 6 inches. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, alternate lifting one leg slightly higher than the other. | Step:4 Continue this fluttering motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Back Lever
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 Bend your knees and tuck them towards your chest. | Step:4 Slowly lift your legs up, keeping them straight, until your body is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the ground slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with your feet elevated on a stable surface. | Step:2 Keep your body in a straight line from head to toe, engaging your core muscles. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapula Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 As you lower, squeeze your shoulder blades together and push your chest forward. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Superman Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower your body, simultaneously lift your right arm and left leg off the ground, extending them straight out. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then lower your arm and leg back down while pushing yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, this time lifting your left arm and right leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Pike
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up towards the bar, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your body forms a 'V' shape, with your legs parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold the position for a moment, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Donkey Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your toes on an elevated surface, such as a step or block. | Step:2 Place your hands on a stable support, such as a wall or railing, for balance. | Step:3 Raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Single Arm Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and one hand placed slightly wider than the other. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, shift your weight to one side and lift the opposite arm off the ground, extending it straight out to the side. | Step:4 Push through your chest and triceps to raise your body back up to the starting position, while simultaneously lowering your extended arm back to the ground. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, alternating the arm you extend with each repetition.

name: Side Lying Hip Adduction (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your bottom arm under your head for support. | Step:3 Engage your adductors and lift your top leg as high as possible without rotating your hips or leaning backward. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Clap Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your core engaged. | Step:3 Push through your palms explosively to propel your body off the ground. | Step:4 While in mid-air, clap your hands together before landing back in the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling Push-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your hands shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, so that your body forms a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your chest is just above the ground, then push back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push-Up (On Box)
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the edge of a box or elevated surface, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the box by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapula Dips
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows and retracting your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to squeeze a pencil between them. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to extend your elbows and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bear Crawl
instructions: Step:1 Start on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips. | Step:2 Lift your knees slightly off the ground, keeping your back flat and your core engaged. | Step:3 Move your right hand and left foot forward simultaneously, followed by your left hand and right foot. | Step:4 Continue crawling forward, alternating your hand and foot movements. | Step:5 Maintain a steady pace and keep your core tight throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Continue for the desired distance or time.

name: Incline Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the elevated surface by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up To Side Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your core engaged. | Step:3 Push back up to the starting position. | Step:4 Shift your weight onto your left hand and rotate your body to the right, lifting your right arm towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Hold the side plank position for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and side plank on the opposite side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Dips Floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair or bench with your hands next to your hips, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the front of the chair with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:3 Straighten your arms, keeping a little bend in your elbows to keep tension on your triceps and off your elbow joints. | Step:4 Slowly bend your elbows to lower your body toward the floor until your elbows are at about a 90-degree angle. | Step:5 Once you reach the bottom of the movement, press down into the chair to straighten your elbows, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Skin The Cat
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a bar with your arms fully extended and your body relaxed. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:3 Continue to lift your legs up and over your head, allowing your body to pass through the arms. | Step:4 Once your legs are fully extended over your head, begin to lower them back down towards the starting position. | Step:5 As you lower your legs, allow your body to pass back through the arms until you are hanging with your arms fully extended again. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Isometric Chest Squeeze
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground, with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles together as hard as you can, while keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, focusing on contracting your chest muscles. | Step:5 Release the squeeze and relax your chest muscles. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Three Bench Dip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Gironda Sternum Chin
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a high bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Engage your lats and biceps to pull your chest up towards the bar, leading with your sternum. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
